  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Dose response relationship among five doses of study drug (4 doses of ALKS 37 and placebo), defined as an increasing proportion of patients exhibiting overall response.</measure>
    <time_frame>4 weeks</time_frame>
    <description>Overall response will be defined using an algorithm that takes into consideration number of complete spontaneous bowel movements, improvement from baseline, and durability of response.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
